// Mock disaster scenario — Singapore CBD / Marina Bay, flash flood + hazmat incident.
// Zone geometry is real, not hand-drawn: the flood zone is pulled from the actual
// Singapore River water polygon (extracted from the mapbox-streets-v8 tileset via
// map.querySourceFeatures, clipped to the Clarke Quay/Boat Quay stretch, then buffered
// slightly to represent overflow), and every shelter is a real building footprint from
// the same tileset. Landmark coordinates came from the SearchBox API, and every
// zone-to-shelter route is a real walking direction from the Mapbox Directions API —
// clicking a hazard zone shows its route to all 4 shelters, clicking a shelter shows
// its route to both hazard zones, with the fastest option highlighted either way.
// The hazmat zone stays a radius circle — that's how real dispersion/evacuation zones
// around a point-source leak are actually drawn.

